  "description": [
    "Mississippi Economic Council Business Speaks Out About Sunday Closing A policy adopted by the Board of Directors of the Mis sissippi Economic Council at its recent fall meeting seems es pecially appropriate to mention at this heavyshopping time of the year Were speaking of the policy deploring the trend to ward a sevenday business week and asking that Sunday closing laws be made more practical and enforceable The policy is even more lau dable when it is considered that It comes from an organization representing business and ev eryone knows that business likes shoppers and a profit But the made scramble for the dollar for seven days a week is not healthy for either the employee or employer even if the mor al issue of taking Sunday as a day of worship is left out Here are a few of th things consider ed by MEC directors in adopting the proposal Mississippis laws regulating Sunday business activities were enacted years before the intro duction of modern transporta tion communications and many day to day services Since our municipal officials are required to enforce a law that is imprac tical violations result in every community every Sunday Offi cials have the"
